The '''Australian Fencing Federation (AFF)''' is the national governing body for the sport of [[fencing]] within [[Australia]]. It was founded in 1949.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://ausfencing.org/home/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=6&Itemid=60|title = The AFF and its Members|date = |access-date = 5 February 2016|website = |publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref>
==Member States== The AFF comprises six member states: * [http://www.actfa.org.au/home/ ACT Fencing Association] * [http://www.nswfencing.org.au/ NSW Fencing Association] * [http://www.qfa.org.au/ Queensland Fencing Association] * [http://www.fencingsa.org.au/ Fencing South Australia] * [http://www.foxsportspulse.com/assoc_page.cgi?assoc=3825&pID=1 Fencing Victoria] * [http://www.fencingwa.com/ Western Australia Fencing Association]
==Life Members== The AFF currently has 23 life members.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.ausfencing.org/home/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1138&Itemid=318|title = AFF Life Members|date = |access-date = 12 March 2016| website = |publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref> * [[Eddis Linton]] * [[Robyn Chaplin]] * Professor [[Joan Beck]] * [[David McKenzie (fencer)|David McKenzie]] AM * [[Max England]] * [[Julius Pollack]] * [[Andy V Szakall]] * [[Ivan Lund]] * [[Laurie Smith (fencer)|Laurie Smith]] * [[Partick Morley (fencer)|Patrick Morley]] * [[Beverley Chan]] * [[Harry Sommerville]] * [[John Fethers]] * Professor [[Micheal O'Brien]] * [[Bill Ronald|William (Bill) Ronald]] OAM * [[Janet Haswell]] * [[Denise Dapre]] OAM * [[Peter Anderson (fencer)|Peter Anderson]] * [[Vivienne Watts (Tucker)]] * [[Helen Smith (fencer)|Helen Smith]] AM * [[Alex Donaldson (fencer)|Alex Donaldson]] * [[Jeff Gray (fencer)|Jeff Gray]] * [[Peter Osvath]]
