'''Barry Woodland''' is a British former [[Grand Prix motorcycle racing|Grand Prix motorcycle road racer]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.iomtoday.co.im/sport/CAVALADE-OF-LEGENDS-TO-MARK.1943787.jp|title=Cavalade of Legends to Mark TT Centenary|date=23 December 2006|work=Isle of Man Today|accessdate=20 July 2010}}</ref>

Woodland won the [[Isle of Man TT]] Production D class three times in a row (1985–1988).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.iomtt.com/TT-Database/Events/Races.aspx?meet_code=ALL&ride_id=3420 |title=Barry Woodland Isle of Man TT results |publisher=iomtt.com |accessdate=13 February 2013}}</ref> His most commonly used bike was the Loctite [[Yamaha Motor Company|Yamaha]]. In 1987 Woodland made it a clean sweep on the Isle of Man circuit for the Loctite Yamaha team by winning Production Class D. He is now retired from motor bike racing.

