{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2017}} {{Use British English|date=April 2017}} {{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Forthill | nickname = | country = Scotland | image = | location = [[Dundee]], [[Scotland]] | establishment = 1911 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1924&ndash;1999 | club1 = [[Scotland national cricket team|Scotland]] | date = 19 October | year = 2011 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/24/1680.html Ground profile }}
'''Forthill''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Dundee]], [[Scotland]]. The first recorded match held on the ground came in 1911 when Fofarshire Cricket Club played [[Essex County Cricket Club|Essex]] during the English counties tour of Scotland.<ref name="OTH">{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/24/1680_misc.html|title=Other matches played on Forthill, Dundee|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=19 October 2011}}</ref> [[Scotland cricket team|Scotland]] first used the ground in 1913 when they played [[Northamptonshire County Cricket Club|Northamptonshire]].<ref name="OTH"/> The ground held its inaugural [[first-class cricket|first-class]] match in 1924 when Scotland played [[Ireland cricket team|Ireland]]. The touring [[India national cricket team|Indians]] played Scotland in a first-class match there in 1932. Almost twenty years elapsed before first-class cricket returned to Forthill, with Scotland playing [[Worcestershire County Cricket Club|Worcestershire]] in 1951. The ground later played host to the touring [[New Zealand national cricket team|New Zealanders]] in 1978 and Ireland in 1992, before hosting its final first-class match when Scotland played the [[South Africa Academy cricket team|South Africa Academy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/24/1680_f.html|title=First-Class Matches played on Forthill, Dundee|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=18 October 2011}}</ref> Throughout the twentieth century the ground hosted several touring teams, though the matches were not rated as first-class.<ref name="OTH"/>
The ground is still in use today by Forfarshire Cricket Club.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.forfarshire.co.uk/|title=Forfarshire Cricket Club|publisher=www.forfarshire.co.uk|accessdate=19 October 2011}}</ref>
