'''Taciana Cesar''' (nee Lima) (born December 17, 1983) is a [[Guinea-Bissau|Bissau-Guinean]] [[judoka]]. She competed at the [[2016 Summer Olympics]] in the [[Judo at the 2016 Summer Olympics – Women's 48 kg|women's 48 kg]] event, in which she was eliminated in the second round by [[Galbadrakhyn Otgontsetseg]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Taciana Lima|url=https://www.rio2016.com/en/athlete/taciana-lima|website=Rio 2016|accessdate=August 17, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160817160724/https://www.rio2016.com/en/athlete/taciana-lima|archivedate=August 17, 2016}}</ref> She was the flag bearer for Guinea-Bissau during the closing ceremony.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.olympic.org/news/the-flagbearers-for-the-rio-2016-closing-ceremony|title=The Flagbearers for the Rio 2016 Closing Ceremony|date=2016-08-21|access-date=2016-08-22}}</ref>
